1
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:00,200
Mr. Gu,

2
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,800
the Commander sent us to pay you a visit.

3
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:04,800
Thank the Commander.

4
00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:07,280
How is your health now?

5
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:11,560
Thanks to the Commander,

6
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:12,720
I am doing well.

7
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,039
This

8
00:01:17,039 --> 00:01:19,039
is a small token from our Commander.

9
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,600
The Commander asked us to tell you,

10
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:24,840
if you need anything, just let him know.

11
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,920
He will do his best to arrange it.

12
00:01:27,039 --> 00:01:28,970
That is very kind of the Commander.

13
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,240
Mr. Gu, we won't disturb you then.

14
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:32,039
Get some rest.

15
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,040
When did you get here?

16
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:06,970
You startled me.

17
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,240
Why are you so jumpy?

18
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,720
You keep saying the house is dirty.

19
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:10,979
But look at this place.

20
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:14,400
You're just in time.

21
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,000
Come here.

22
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,079
What's wrong?

23
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,210
The patient in the next ward seems to be faking it.

24
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,200
Faking it?

25
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,160
What illness?

26
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,250
I don't know the specifics yet.

27
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,160
But that guy looks sneaky.

28
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,579
I think he's definitely up to something.

29
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,329
Tell Bao to look into him when you get back.

30
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:40,960
Do you want an orange?

31
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:10,840
Hide.

32
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,880
Let's go.

33
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:56,800
Waiting for me?

34
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:57,760
Let's go.

35
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:02,320
This place isn't cheap.

36
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,380
How much does a visit cost?

37
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:09,170
At least half your monthly salary.

38
00:04:12,040 --> 00:04:12,720
Then,

39
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:14,320
I can only come twice a month.

40
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,380
What are you thinking?

41
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,480
I'm not wrong.

42
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,640
The math is right.

43
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,330
Who's in the special care ward?

44
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:25,800
Tell me.

45
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,560
As far as I know,

46
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,920
the one supposed to be living here is

47
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,680
the former secretary of the Army Chief of Staff,

48
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:35,480
Gu Zhiting.

49
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,560
You are his attending physician.

50
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,090
You should know about this.

51
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,240
As a doctor,

52
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,770
it's very hard to get into Guangren Hospital.

53
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,970
I wonder if the hospital found out,

54
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,920
would it affect Dr. Sun's job?

55
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:58,640
Actually,

56
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:02,180
Master Gu passed away half a year ago.

57
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,120
The one in the ward

58
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,960
is his son, Gu Zhang.

59
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,360
Hang in there, Dad.

60
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,720
Atropine 0.5.

61
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:14,560
Quick.

62
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,620
Hang in there, Dad.

63
00:05:18,760 --> 00:05:19,820
Hang in there, Dad.

64
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:22,840
Hold on.

65
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:38,720
Doctor,

66
00:05:39,159 --> 00:05:41,360
Doctor, please find a way to save my dad.

67
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:42,200
Doctor,

68
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,520
I beg you.

69
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:44,800
I beg you, Doctor.

70
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,040
I beg you.

71
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,760
I beg you, save my dad.

72
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:50,560
Dad, wake up.

73
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:53,560
I'm sorry for your loss.

74
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,840
Wake up, Dad.

75
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,120
Wake up, Dad!

76
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,440
You can't die.

77
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:01,160
Dr. Sun.

78
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:02,240
Dr. Sun.

79
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,160
What are you doing?

80
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:03,840
Dr. Sun,

81
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,400
promise me one thing.

82
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,240
Get up first, then we'll talk.

83
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:06,880
No.

84
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:07,720
If you don't promise,

85
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,520
I won't get up.

86
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:09,690
Go ahead.

87
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:10,720
Please,

88
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,260
don't let anyone know my father died.

89
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:15,480
What did you say?

90
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,040
Dr. Sun, you know

91
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:19,970
my father lives here

92
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,960
and gets a government subsidy every month.

93
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:23,880
I'm useless.

94
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,280
My whole family relies on

95
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,040
my dad's subsidy to survive.

96
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,200
If my dad dies,

97
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,640
the subsidy is gone,

98
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,360
and my family won't be able to survive.

99
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,560
Dr. Sun, please.

100
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,280
Get up. Please.

101
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,040
Dr. Sun.

102
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,280
This isn't a joke.

103
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,360
Listen to me.

104
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,040
I can pretend to be my dad.

105
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,400
Are you kidding?

106
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,200
No way.

107
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,320
Dr. Sun,

108
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,050
listen to me.

109
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,400
Ever since I was little,

110
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,460
everyone said I look just like my dad.

111
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,080
Don't worry.

112
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:48,960
As long as I pretend to be him,

113
00:06:48,960 --> 00:06:50,000
no one will be able to tell.

114
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,320
Mr. Gu has passed away.

115
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,720
You can't hide this.

116
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,840
But without this subsidy,

117
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,360
my whole family

118
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,600
won't be able to survive.

119
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,680
Dr. Sun, you're a doctor.

120
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,520
You can't just leave us to die, can you?

121
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,600
It's fine if I die,

122
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,920
but I have a child.

123
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,520
When he was born,

124
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,320
he had heart problems.

125
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:10,480
The doctor said he wouldn't live past six.

126
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,200
But all these years,

127
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,280
I've tried everything

128
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,000
and spent all our savings

129
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,280
just to keep him alive.

130
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,040
Doctor,

131
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:17,920
I beg you.

132
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,640
This is a hospital.

133
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,360
He turns six next month.

134
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,250
He turns six next month.

135
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,040
Do you realize that doing this,

136
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,400
if you get caught,

137
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,560
not only will you lose your license,

138
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,720
but you'll also go to prison?

139
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,000
Of course I know.

140
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,520
But if I didn't help him,

141
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,680
his child would truly be hopeless.

142
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:39,040
I am a doctor.

143
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:41,159
I couldn't just stand by and watch them die.

144
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:42,120
So tell me, Doctor,

145
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:42,880
how did you handle

146
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,520
Gu Zhiting's body?

147
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,560
I didn't handle that.

148
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,560
Gu Zhang moved the body himself.

149
00:07:52,159 --> 00:07:54,690
I heard he buried it in their ancestral grave.

150
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:57,120
Has no one suspected anything for the past six months?

151
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,480
Once disguised,

152
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,240
he really can pass for the real thing.

153
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,040
Plus,

154
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,000
he stays in bed during the day

155
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:05,690
and only goes home occasionally at night.

156
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,530
Does Director Cao know about this?

157
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,880
Of course not.

158
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,360
Director Cao is a man of integrity.

159
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,560
If he knew,

160
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,210
he certainly wouldn't let him keep up the act.

161
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,000
Dr. Sun,

162
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,200
regarding you and Gu Zhang,

163
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:25,930
we can keep your secret for now.

164
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,720
We also hope that regarding our talk today,

165
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,640
you can pretend it never happened.

166
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,440
Okay.

167
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,960
Thank you. I understand.

168
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:33,919
Thank you.

169
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,280
It seems

170
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:45,560
she doesn't know Gu Zhang is sleeping around.

171
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:46,440
If you ask me,

172
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,320
it's not even certain if Gu Zhang

173
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,920
actually has a wife and kids.

174
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,770
We should play the long game

175
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,800
and see what he's hiding from us.

176
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:57,440
If Director Cao knew about Gu Zhang,

177
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:00,210
then it's very likely Gu Zhang killed him.

178
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:02,740
I just did the math.

179
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,680
Gu Zhiting's monthly subsidy is

180
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,720
150 yuan.

181
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:08,040
After deducting hospital fees,

182
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:11,280
it's not enough to cover Gu Zhang's spending at the dance hall.

183
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,880
Where did Gu Zhang get the money

184
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:14,610
to go to the dance hall so often?

185
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:17,050
What I don't understand is,

186
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:20,770
if Director Cao knew Gu Zhang was impersonating his father,

187
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,840
why didn't he expose him?

188
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,610
What's on your mind?

189
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,050
I was just thinking,

190
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:34,040
if Gu Zhang really killed Director Cao,

191
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,240
with so many people in the hospital,

192
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,100
how did he manage to go unnoticed?

193
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:42,920
I got Gu Zhang's address.

194
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:45,020
And there's an unexpected bonus.

195
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,320
At Shiliupu's Old Water Bug Wharf,

196
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:50,000
a new batch of foreign goods arrived recently.

197
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,560
They say it's miracle medicine from Guangren Hospital.

198
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:53,880
Gu Zhang is stealing medicine to sell.

199
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,000
That explains it.

200
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:58,100
Guangren Hospital's medicine costs a fortune.

201
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,280
Let's go check it out in a bit.

202
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,400
You guys go check it out.

203
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,200
I have to return to the hospital.

204
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,200
Come on, let's do this together.

205
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,260
Here's to Linlan's speedy recovery.

206
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,880
I beg you, please stop coming here.

207
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,340
He ran away a long time ago.

208
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,240
You're making such a scene.

209
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,800
We can't get any peace.

210
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:27,240
We're from the Central Police Station.

211
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:30,720
So you're not here to collect debts?

212
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,880
We just wanted to ask,

213
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,000
is this the Gu residence?

214
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,760
Yes, it is.

215
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,640
But he ran away a long time ago.

216
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:36,600
How long has he been gone?

217
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:37,760
Over half a year.

218
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:39,880
God knows how much money that Gu bastard

219
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:41,360
owes to loan sharks.

220
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,680
Every other day, some gangsters

221
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,560
show up with axes,

222
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,280
blocking the back of our alley.

223
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,800
Having a neighbor like that

224
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,400
must be punishment for our past sins.

225
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:51,060
What about his wife and child?

226
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:54,160
How could a bastard like him afford a wife?

227
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:56,600
If his father didn't have a government job,

228
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,600
he would have starved to death long ago.

229
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:01,200
Are you used to the new medicine we prescribed?

230
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:02,360
Yes, I am.

231
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,760
As long as you follow the treatment course,

232
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,160
you'll recover quickly.

233
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,640
Also, drink more milk

234
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,600
and eat nutritious foods like eggs.

235
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,080
Eat more fruit, too.

236
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,320
Thank you for your care all this time.

237
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:15,960
It's our duty.

238
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,060
Actually, seeing you recover so well

239
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,640
makes us very happy.

240
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:21,960
Thank you.

241
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,360
What's wrong?

242
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:24,800
Mr. Gu,

243
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:25,850
are you okay?

244
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:27,640
I'm sorry.

245
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,400
Be careful.

246
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:30,960
I'm really sorry.

247
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,720
Just wipe it off, kid.

248
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,080
Mr. Gu,

249
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,480
let me take you to get cleaned up.

250
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,080
Okay.

251
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,500
Sorry for the trouble.

252
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,570
Watch your step, Mr. Gu.

253
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:47,640
Bao.

254
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:50,360
Brother,

255
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:52,440
do you have any white potion?

256
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,880
What white potion?

257
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,400
This is a freight warehouse.

258
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,400
Go to a pharmacy if you want medicine.

259
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,440
What are you doing?

260
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:00,840
He just thought you had foreign goods here.

261
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,560
You two want this, right?

262
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:05,440
I have it.

263
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:06,760
Wait a moment.

264
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:21,680
Don't run.

265
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:26,760
Get up.

266
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:28,180
Don't move.

267
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,000
Officer,

268
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,840
I only sell this medicine to our own brothers.

269
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,600
I'm not selling it to just anyone.

270
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,360
Spare my life, hero.

271
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,880
Where did this medicine come from?

272
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:38,800
I bought it at Guangren Hospital.

273
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,040
From time to time,

274
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,680
someone there brings medicine out to sell.

275
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:42,720
Who sold it to you?

276
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,520
They said it was a nurse in the pharmacy.

277
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:45,980
Are you sure it was a woman?

278
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,640
I'm telling the truth.

279
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:50,570
Can't I tell the difference between a man and a woman?

280
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,200
I see.

281
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:04,930
Gu Zhang.

282
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,480
I found this in the suitcase

283
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:08,680
under his bed.

284
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:11,780
It's very likely that Gu Zhang killed Director Cao.

285
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,000
Since he was wearing a nurse's uniform,

286
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:14,960
and it was night,

287
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,880
no one noticed him at all.

288
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:18,720
What now?

289
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,200
Let's catch him first.

290
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,280
Please, Director.

291
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:23,360
I beg you.

292
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:25,560
My child is only six, Director.

293
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,160
Director.

294
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:39,880
Where is he?

295
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,880
He was just here.

296
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:44,920
Bao.

297
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:46,040
Send everyone out.

298
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,580
We must bring him back.

299
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:55,120
You're back, Inspector Lin.

300
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,240
Inspector Lin is back.

301
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:59,170
Long time no see.

302
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:07,700
Inspector Lin.

303
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,320
We received a report.

304
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:12,050
A male body was found in a garret on Xujiahui Road.

305
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:32,280
The deceased's face is purple and swollen.

306
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:34,760
The ligature mark is an open horseshoe shape,

307
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:36,040
slanting up behind the ears,

308
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,770
deep in the flesh and unbroken.

309
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:41,000
There is bruising around the mark,

310
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,360
and extensive subcutaneous bleeding.

311
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:44,400
It fits the characteristics of death by hanging.

312
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,880
The jaw is stiff.

313
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,600
The finger joints are slightly stiff.

314
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,960
Time of death is

315
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:50,880
about eight to ten hours ago.

316
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:52,820
No scratches on the hands.

317
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:54,320
Fingernails are clean.

318
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,850
No defensive wounds found.

319
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:58,370
Found this on the table.

320
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:04,180
My father passed away.

321
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,319
He deserved a grand funeral,

322
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,730
but was buried in haste.

323
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:09,760
I acted as an imposter,

324
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,250
unworthy of being a son,

325
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:13,210
just for a few pieces of silver.

326
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,040
I was obsessed,

327
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:16,200
possessed,

328
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,920
killed Director Cao,

329
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:19,720
and tried to escape punishment.

330
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,560
I know my sins are heavy,

331
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:23,200
and my conscience is uneasy.

332
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,119
Only death

333
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,160
can atone for my life.

334
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,680
Let's close the case.

335
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,370
We can't close the case.

336
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:34,600
Why?

337
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,360
Because the investigation isn't over yet.

338
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,930
What else is there to investigate?

339
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:42,480
The crime scene records,

340
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:43,320
autopsy report,

341
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:44,980
and suicide note are all here.

342
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,600
Why keep investigating?

343
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,440
We just found the evidence,

344
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:49,480
and he killed himself.

345
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,410
Isn't that a bit too coincidental?

346
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,360
Listen, Lin Lan.

347
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:57,880
Have you been reading too many detective novels?

348
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:59,880
There aren't that many coincidences.

349
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:00,610
Case closed.

350
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:01,560
You guys,

351
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:03,620
go home early and get some rest today.

352
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,760
Do you think it was suicide?

353
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,360
There were no other external injuries on the body,

354
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:16,960
nor were there defensive wounds.

355
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:18,760
Also, the ligature marks on his neck

356
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:20,420
are consistent with the rope.

357
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:24,620
This really fits all the characteristics of a suicide.

358
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,700
What about you two?

359
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,620
I've asked the neighbors.

360
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,620
No one heard any noise from his house last night.

361
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:36,960
At the scene,

362
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:40,200
there really are no signs of struggle or fighting.

363
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,120
And the evidence and motive

364
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,520
are all very reasonable.

365
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:45,360
But why did this shameless jerk

366
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,680
commit suicide?

367
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:49,240
I just can't figure out right now

368
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,200
why he suddenly killed himself.

369
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,240
Did Doctor Sun

370
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:55,000
tell him about being interrogated,

371
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,400
so he killed himself to escape punishment?

372
00:18:58,120 --> 00:18:58,920
Unlikely.

373
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,840
Before we found this nurse uniform,

374
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:03,840
we hadn't found any other evidence.

375
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,000
If he knew we were investigating him,

376
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,040
shouldn't he have

377
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,040
tried to destroy the nurse uniform first

378
00:19:09,040 --> 00:19:10,560
instead of leaving it in the box?
